<p>I have a receiver to catch events. Here is my receiver:</p>  <pre><code>public class CalendarReminderReceiver extends BroadcastReceiver {     @Override     public void onReceive(Context context, Intent intent) {         if (intent.getAction().equalsIgnoreCase(CalendarContract.ACTION_EVENT_REMINDER)) {             Log.d("test", "reminder fired");         }     } } </code></pre>  <p>And here is my <code>manifest.xml</code>:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;receiver android:name=".CalendarReminderReceiver"&gt;             &lt;intent-filter&gt;                 &lt;action android:name="android.intent.action.EVENT_REMINDER" /&gt;                 &lt;data android:scheme="content" /&gt;             &lt;/intent-filter&gt; &lt;/receiver&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The problem is the log appears in logcat multiple times (six times). I tested on lollipop and kitkat and in both devices receiver fired 6 times. What is the problem?</p>